WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.380 --> 00:00:05.547
.

2
00:00:05.630 --> 00:00:06.881
- Previously on
"The Hunting Party"...

3
00:00:07.549 --> 00:00:09.009
- It's called The Pit.

4
00:00:09.092 --> 00:00:10.343
It's home to the most dangerous
and violent criminals

5
00:00:10.427 --> 00:00:13.013
in history. all of whom
the world believes are dead.

6
00:00:13.179 --> 00:00:17.100
Or at least it was
until the blast hit.

7
00:00:17.225 --> 00:00:18.518
- Shane deserved
to know the truth.

8
00:00:18.560 --> 00:00:19.686
- What are you
going to tell him?

9
00:00:19.811 --> 00:00:21.146
Hey. we found your
serial killer mom.

10
00:00:21.229 --> 00:00:22.480
and she happens to be our boss?

11
00:00:22.605 --> 00:00:24.232
- I don't know.
but I'll find the right words.

12
00:00:24.357 --> 00:00:25.900
- You were impressive.

13
00:00:26.067 --> 00:00:27.944
- Thank you. sir.

14
00:00:28.028 --> 00:00:29.904
- And my name's John.
by the way.

15
00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:31.573
- Jonathan Mitchell Peck.

16
00:00:31.740 --> 00:00:32.866
I read your file.

17
00:00:32.907 --> 00:00:34.367
- I've been thinking
a lot about that.

18
00:00:34.451 --> 00:00:36.369
and I should never have kept
that from you or the team.

19
00:00:36.453 --> 00:00:37.620
I am done looking for her.

20
00:00:37.746 --> 00:00:38.997
- You don't want
to find your mom?

21
00:00:39.122 --> 00:00:40.081
- Welcome.

22
00:00:40.206 --> 00:00:43.835
My name is Noah Cyrus.

23
00:00:43.918 --> 00:00:45.420
[gunfire]

24
00:00:47.672 --> 00:00:49.716
[slow tempo music]

25
00:00:49.799 --> 00:00:51.634
[horn honks]

26
00:00:51.718 --> 00:00:54.137
♪ ♪

27
00:00:54.262 --> 00:00:57.015
[coffee maker screeching]

28
00:00:57.098 --> 00:00:59.392
- ♪ Trouble ♪

29
00:00:59.476 --> 00:01:01.019
- Ooh. wait.

30
00:01:01.102 --> 00:01:02.228
Can you make one of those
heart design things?

31
00:01:02.312 --> 00:01:03.480
I want to post it.

32
00:01:03.521 --> 00:01:04.981
Maybe a star.

33
00:01:05.106 --> 00:01:07.984
No. wait. a flower.
like an orchid.

34
00:01:08.068 --> 00:01:10.779
- They don't really teach us
how to do that.

35
00:01:10.862 --> 00:01:12.947
I can make a swirl.

36
00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:14.908
- That's just so basic.

37
00:01:14.991 --> 00:01:17.911
Just try a flower.

38
00:01:17.994 --> 00:01:19.662
- It's already half swirl.

39
00:01:19.829 --> 00:01:21.915
- I mean. if you have to make
a fresh one. it's totally fine.

40
00:01:21.998 --> 00:01:22.999
I will pay for it.

41
00:01:23.041 --> 00:01:24.042
- Do you mind?

42
00:01:24.125 --> 00:01:25.669
There are other people in line.

43
00:01:25.794 --> 00:01:27.921
[notification chimes]
- Oh. shoot.

44
00:01:28.046 --> 00:01:30.006
Oh. my gosh. I forgot that
I have Hot Yoga in 15.

45
00:01:30.048 --> 00:01:31.216
Don't worry though.

46
00:01:31.299 --> 00:01:32.634
When I post this.
I'm going to totally

47
00:01:32.759 --> 00:01:33.802
make your cafe go viral.

48
00:01:36.638 --> 00:01:38.723
- Sorry for that.
What can I get you?

49
00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:40.850
- Hi. Drip coffee. please.

50
00:01:40.892 --> 00:01:42.060
[dramatic music]

51
00:01:42.143 --> 00:01:43.645
- TotesTina here.

52
00:01:43.687 --> 00:01:46.564
And it is time to reveal
the newest addition

53
00:01:46.648 --> 00:01:49.025
to Tina's Less to Impress list.

54
00:01:49.109 --> 00:01:51.194
First off.
I need you guys to go--

55
00:01:51.236 --> 00:01:53.029
no. not go. run--

56
00:01:53.113 --> 00:01:55.573
to the cutest new coffee bar
I just found.

57
00:01:55.657 --> 00:01:57.158
Bernice's Coffee.

58
00:01:57.283 --> 00:01:59.911
No. seriously. people.
it's the best oat milk latte

59
00:01:59.994 --> 00:02:01.996
I've had all year.

60
00:02:02.038 --> 00:02:05.917
Whoever's feeling blessed.
say "blessed."

61
00:02:06.042 --> 00:02:08.628
Also. this new raspberry
lip gloss. ugh.

62
00:02:08.670 --> 00:02:10.213
it makes my lips just feel so--

63
00:02:10.296 --> 00:02:11.172
[shouts]

64
00:02:11.256 --> 00:02:13.883
[horn honks]

65
00:02:13.967 --> 00:02:16.886
[suspenseful music]

66
00:02:16.970 --> 00:02:20.849
♪ ♪

67
00:02:20.932 --> 00:02:22.726
[indistinct chatter]

68
00:02:22.809 --> 00:02:25.729
- Hey. did Peck tell you
what this was all about?

69
00:02:25.895 --> 00:02:28.231
- Uh. no. but when I get a call
to come to the Command Center.

70
00:02:28.314 --> 00:02:29.649
it's usually not for breakfast.

71
00:02:29.691 --> 00:02:30.567
- Right.
but when it's an inmate.

72
00:02:30.650 --> 00:02:33.069
I always get a heads up.

73
00:02:33.111 --> 00:02:34.112
- You didn't?

74
00:02:34.195 --> 00:02:35.280
♪ ♪

75
00:02:35.321 --> 00:02:37.323
- As Agent Hasani will explain.

76
00:02:37.407 --> 00:02:39.284
we have a problem.

77
00:02:40.618 --> 00:02:42.037
- Last night. the convoy

78
00:02:42.078 --> 00:02:44.330
transporting Noah Cyrus
was attacked.

79
00:02:44.414 --> 00:02:47.625
Everyone. including Cyrus.
was killed.

80
00:02:47.667 --> 00:02:48.918
[suspenseful music]

81
00:02:49.002 --> 00:02:50.378
- Do we know who did it?

82
00:02:50.503 --> 00:02:52.213
- Why would somebody do this?

83
00:02:52.297 --> 00:02:53.923
Could have been one
of Cyrus' followers

84
00:02:54.090 --> 00:02:55.592
that we didn't know about?

85
00:02:55.717 --> 00:02:57.719
- This is way too complicated
for someone of the 13th Hour.

86
00:02:57.802 --> 00:02:59.387
- Who else knows
about the convoys?

87
00:02:59.471 --> 00:03:00.638
- Just my people at CIA.

88
00:03:00.722 --> 00:03:03.683
- Well. clearly.
you're mistaken.

89
00:03:03.725 --> 00:03:05.977
Someone outside of this command

90
00:03:06.061 --> 00:03:08.229
knew exactly when
and where to ambush

91
00:03:08.313 --> 00:03:09.856
a covert prisoner transport.

92
00:03:10.023 --> 00:03:12.567
So either a member of your team
is talking

93
00:03:12.734 --> 00:03:13.943
or one of you is.

94
00:03:14.069 --> 00:03:18.198
♪ ♪

95
00:03:18.323 --> 00:03:19.491
- Colonel--

96
00:03:19.616 --> 00:03:21.534
- As it stands.
the Pentagon has insisted

97
00:03:21.618 --> 00:03:23.578
upon a certain balance
of powers

98
00:03:23.703 --> 00:03:25.038
in the recovery efforts.

99
00:03:25.080 --> 00:03:27.916
So that means.
Agent Hasani.

100
00:03:27.999 --> 00:03:29.751
prisoner transport
and relocation remains

101
00:03:29.834 --> 00:03:33.505
under your purview. for now.

102
00:03:33.588 --> 00:03:35.674
I don't think I need to
impress upon you all

103
00:03:35.757 --> 00:03:37.801
the seriousness
of this operational failure.

104
00:03:37.926 --> 00:03:42.097
♪ ♪

105
00:03:42.222 --> 00:03:43.932
- Sorry to interrupt. Colonel.

106
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:45.975
We just got a hit
on another inmate.

107
00:03:46.101 --> 00:03:48.103
♪ ♪

108
00:03:48.186 --> 00:03:49.813
- No more mistakes.

109
00:03:49.854 --> 00:03:51.356
I expect perfection.

110
00:03:51.481 --> 00:03:52.315
Dismissed.

111
00:03:52.440 --> 00:03:57.320
♪ ♪

112
00:03:57.445 --> 00:04:00.407
- Inmate H89. Lou Kaplan.

113
00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:02.450
- A.K.A.. the Selfie Slayer.

114
00:04:02.534 --> 00:04:04.577
- Not to brag. but low-key.

115
00:04:04.703 --> 00:04:06.955
I created a program
to alert me if any inmates.

116
00:04:07.080 --> 00:04:09.165
logged on to their dormant
social media platforms.

117
00:04:09.332 --> 00:04:10.917
- Wow. that's very clever.

118
00:04:11.042 --> 00:04:12.585
- Thank you.

119
00:04:12.711 --> 00:04:14.254
It uses malware software
I designed to bypass VPNs.

120
00:04:14.421 --> 00:04:18.049
It looks like Lou just
logged on to his old

121
00:04:18.174 --> 00:04:21.302
SnapMax account
for the first time since 2019

122
00:04:21.386 --> 00:04:23.179
in Midtown Manhattan.

123
00:04:23.263 --> 00:04:25.974
I guess even Pit inmates
can't stay off social media.

124
00:04:26.016 --> 00:04:27.183
- SnapMax.
that's the one that's. like.

125
00:04:27.267 --> 00:04:28.852
if Instagram and TikTok
had a baby. right?

126
00:04:28.935 --> 00:04:30.687
- Well. I don't know.

127
00:04:30.770 --> 00:04:33.023
We have a strict no social
media policy at my house.

128
00:04:33.106 --> 00:04:34.357
- That's fun.

129
00:04:34.441 --> 00:04:36.860
- It says here that Lou
was a gifted coder

130
00:04:36.901 --> 00:04:39.362
and one of the original
software designers for SnapMax.

131
00:04:39.446 --> 00:04:42.157
He had some pretty lofty ideals
about social media

132
00:04:42.240 --> 00:04:44.951
fostering community
and empathy.

133
00:04:45.035 --> 00:04:46.536
- I'm sensing a turn coming.

134
00:04:46.661 --> 00:04:48.246
- Well.
he wanted his technology

135
00:04:48.329 --> 00:04:49.706
to bring people together.

136
00:04:49.789 --> 00:04:52.250
Instead. according to him.
the app. quote.

137
00:04:52.334 --> 00:04:55.086
"Became a breeding ground
for vanity. vitriol.

138
00:04:55.128 --> 00:04:58.131
and self-isolating behavior."

139
00:04:58.214 --> 00:05:00.467
- So I'm guessing the nickname
the Selfie Slayer

140
00:05:00.550 --> 00:05:01.593
is not a metaphor.

141
00:05:01.634 --> 00:05:02.761
- His M.O. is interesting.

142
00:05:02.886 --> 00:05:04.304
Despite the fact
that he carefully selected

143
00:05:04.387 --> 00:05:06.514
and then stalked
these victims for days.

144
00:05:06.598 --> 00:05:08.600
the kills themselves
were semi-improvised

145
00:05:08.683 --> 00:05:10.435
and always public.

146
00:05:10.560 --> 00:05:12.395
This one.
he threw into oncoming traffic

147
00:05:12.520 --> 00:05:13.897
as she was livestreaming.

148
00:05:14.022 --> 00:05:14.981
And then another.
he beat to death

149
00:05:15.023 --> 00:05:17.484
in Prospect Park
using his own tripod.

150
00:05:17.609 --> 00:05:19.527
- He claimed that
his six murders were a message.

151
00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:20.820
a way to wake the world up
to the dangers

152
00:05:20.945 --> 00:05:21.988
of social media.

153
00:05:22.030 --> 00:05:23.865
- The Post wrote
a whole exposé on him.

154
00:05:23.990 --> 00:05:26.701
turning him into a social media
sensation himself.

155
00:05:26.743 --> 00:05:29.204
an ironic poster child
for disruption.

156
00:05:29.287 --> 00:05:30.997
They even had merch
with his face on it

157
00:05:31.081 --> 00:05:32.707
outside the courthouse
during his trial.

158
00:05:32.874 --> 00:05:33.833
- Gross.
- Gross.

159
00:05:33.917 --> 00:05:35.126
- Gross.
- Yeah.

160
00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:36.753
- If he's already logged
back into SnapMax again.

161
00:05:36.878 --> 00:05:38.797
he's probably stalking victims.

162
00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:40.799
- Let's head out.

163
00:05:40.840 --> 00:05:43.593
[suspenseful music]

164
00:05:43.635 --> 00:05:45.970
- OK. time to shine.

165
00:05:46.054 --> 00:05:48.139
[sighs]

166
00:05:48.223 --> 00:05:49.724
Just remember. be bright.

167
00:05:49.766 --> 00:05:50.934
Be bold.

168
00:05:51.017 --> 00:05:53.103
Be Becky.

169
00:05:53.186 --> 00:05:54.562
[blows]

170
00:05:54.646 --> 00:05:57.023
Ahh.

171
00:05:57.107 --> 00:05:59.317
- ♪ Oh. please ♪

172
00:05:59.401 --> 00:06:01.444
- Hello. fellow bakers.

173
00:06:01.528 --> 00:06:03.613
It's your friend.
Baking with Becky.

174
00:06:03.697 --> 00:06:05.907
And today. I've got
a big treat for you all.

175
00:06:05.990 --> 00:06:08.743
We're making
banana nut muffins.

176
00:06:08.785 --> 00:06:10.495
Now.

177
00:06:10.537 --> 00:06:12.622
I know these look a bit ripe.

178
00:06:12.664 --> 00:06:13.665
Don't you worry.

179
00:06:13.748 --> 00:06:16.084
That's the secret to yum.

180
00:06:16.167 --> 00:06:17.961
But before we start.
I want to make sure

181
00:06:18.003 --> 00:06:19.879
you hit that Subscribe button
to stay in the loop

182
00:06:19.963 --> 00:06:21.548
for all my best new recipes.

183
00:06:21.631 --> 00:06:24.300
All right. it's baking time.

184
00:06:24.384 --> 00:06:26.219
Now. you're gonna want to start

185
00:06:26.261 --> 00:06:28.972
with two cups
of all-purpose flour.

186
00:06:29.097 --> 00:06:31.266
♪ ♪

187
00:06:31.349 --> 00:06:34.269
- Next. we're gonna crack
two eggs.

188
00:06:34.394 --> 00:06:36.312
[suspenseful music]

189
00:06:36.354 --> 00:06:38.815
[sighs] Damn it.

190
00:06:38.940 --> 00:06:41.359
♪ ♪

191
00:06:41.443 --> 00:06:43.611
[sighs]

192
00:06:43.695 --> 00:06:45.864
Take seven.

193
00:06:45.947 --> 00:06:47.991
[sighs]

194
00:06:48.033 --> 00:06:49.117
[dramatic music]

195
00:06:49.159 --> 00:06:51.661
[shouting]

196
00:06:51.703 --> 00:06:54.122
- [shushing]

197
00:06:54.205 --> 00:06:57.083
[airplane whirring]

198
00:06:59.919 --> 00:07:02.005
- You guys get the feeling
Lazarus knows more

199
00:07:02.088 --> 00:07:05.633
about this convoy hit
than she's letting on?

200
00:07:05.759 --> 00:07:08.678
- I mean. her pointing fingers
at us is definitely theater.

201
00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:10.305
She knows something.

202
00:07:10.347 --> 00:07:12.223
- So do I.

203
00:07:12.265 --> 00:07:14.684
Cyrus's convoy deviated from
its planned route last night.

204
00:07:14.809 --> 00:07:16.811
♪ ♪

205
00:07:16.895 --> 00:07:19.064
- Maybe they saw
the attack coming?

206
00:07:19.147 --> 00:07:23.109
- Well. there was no report of
contact before the firefight.

207
00:07:23.151 --> 00:07:25.570
- OK. so now we have
two mysteries--

208
00:07:25.612 --> 00:07:27.739
who attacked the convoy

209
00:07:27.822 --> 00:07:29.824
and how it got deviated
in the first place.

210
00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:31.743
[suspenseful music]

211
00:07:31.826 --> 00:07:33.870
♪ ♪

212
00:07:33.912 --> 00:07:35.747
[electronic beep]

213
00:07:35.789 --> 00:07:38.541
[suspenseful music]

214
00:07:38.583 --> 00:07:40.543
- [breathes shakily]

215
00:07:40.669 --> 00:07:47.592
♪ ♪

216
00:07:47.676 --> 00:07:49.719
- What comes next?

217
00:07:49.761 --> 00:07:51.846
- The eggs?

218
00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:54.015
- Then why are you
looking at me?

219
00:07:54.182 --> 00:07:55.558
Crack the eggs.

220
00:07:55.684 --> 00:07:57.268
- [sighs]

221
00:07:57.352 --> 00:08:01.064
♪ ♪

222
00:08:01.147 --> 00:08:02.232
- [sighs]

223
00:08:02.357 --> 00:08:07.904
♪ ♪

224
00:08:08.029 --> 00:08:10.949
- [cries]

225
00:08:13.493 --> 00:08:14.869
- Bravo.

226
00:08:17.122 --> 00:08:18.248
OK. now say it.

227
00:08:18.373 --> 00:08:21.084
♪ ♪

228
00:08:21.126 --> 00:08:24.045
- [breathes shakily]

229
00:08:24.087 --> 00:08:25.296
Ah!

230
00:08:25.380 --> 00:08:26.631
[gasping]

231
00:08:28.008 --> 00:08:29.801
- Becky.

232
00:08:29.884 --> 00:08:32.387
say it.

233
00:08:32.512 --> 00:08:34.389
- [breathes shakily] OK.

234
00:08:36.141 --> 00:08:37.976
Hi. everyone.

235
00:08:38.059 --> 00:08:40.103
This is gonna be my final post.

236
00:08:40.228 --> 00:08:41.563
- [moans]

237
00:08:43.815 --> 00:08:46.609
[dramatic music]

238
00:08:46.735 --> 00:08:53.742
♪ ♪

239
00:09:02.250 --> 00:09:02.417
.

240
00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:03.918
[airplane whirring]

241
00:09:04.919 --> 00:09:06.629
- I want to try
to put this in terms

242
00:09:06.713 --> 00:09:10.842
that someone as simple
as you can understand.

243
00:09:10.925 --> 00:09:15.347
I had the biggest tech
companies in the entire world

244
00:09:15.388 --> 00:09:18.141
engaged in heated bidding wars

245
00:09:18.224 --> 00:09:20.310
to bring me to their teams.
right?

246
00:09:20.435 --> 00:09:22.228
Instead. I chose SnapMax.

247
00:09:22.312 --> 00:09:24.606
a no-name startup.

248
00:09:24.689 --> 00:09:27.692
because I believed
in their mission.

249
00:09:27.817 --> 00:09:30.195
Also. Linda Cranston
personally came to my home

250
00:09:30.320 --> 00:09:32.447
and practically begged me
on her hands and knees

251
00:09:32.572 --> 00:09:34.699
to work for her.

252
00:09:34.741 --> 00:09:38.536
We designed SnapMax as a tool
to help our users connect.

253
00:09:38.620 --> 00:09:41.790
But after SnapMax launched.
a very unfortunate truth

254
00:09:41.873 --> 00:09:44.000
became abundantly clear
to me--

255
00:09:44.084 --> 00:09:48.296
most people are basically rats.

256
00:09:48.380 --> 00:09:50.465
But it's worse than that
because we have

257
00:09:50.548 --> 00:09:53.635
the intellectual capacity.

258
00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:57.180
but we don't use it.

259
00:09:57.222 --> 00:09:59.683
All the likes. and the clicks.
and the comments.

260
00:09:59.724 --> 00:10:01.142
and the shares.

261
00:10:01.184 --> 00:10:04.145
jonesing for another hit
of dopamine. right?

262
00:10:04.187 --> 00:10:05.480
Just click. click.
click. click. click.

263
00:10:05.563 --> 00:10:07.107
just for dopamine.

264
00:10:07.232 --> 00:10:08.483
Just a little hit.

265
00:10:08.566 --> 00:10:11.277
Tell me.
are you on social media?

266
00:10:11.319 --> 00:10:13.530
Yeah. of course you are.
[chuckles]

267
00:10:13.655 --> 00:10:15.240
- This guy seems like
a real winner.

268
00:10:15.323 --> 00:10:16.408
